@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place 'Bricky' where you want
on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files or
Libraries are needed. The only requirement is that your Workbench must
have 8 colours or more.

                             How to play?

  Bricky is played on a triangular shaped board which contains 66 empty
spaces. The idea is to fill all empty spaces with bricks that have
various patterns. Bricks can be placed anywhere on the lowest row or on
top of another brick.

  To play, just click on one of the empty spaces, if a brick can go
there, then the next brick shown on the right of the game board (in the
'Next' box) will go to the space you clicked on and a new brick will be
shown as the next brick.

  When placing bricks, avoid getting two or more bricks of the same
pattern next to each other, as they would 'explode' and be removed from
the board.

  Try to complete the game in the least amount of moves possible.

  You can restart a game anytime by clicking on the @{b}New Game@{ub} button.

  Have fun!

